ABUJA – Former Minister of Foreign Affairs, Professor Ibrahim Gambari, has been appointed the new Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari, according to unconfirmed reports from Abuja. One of the reports, by THISDAY, said that Gambari, who was Buhari’s Foreign Minister and confidant as military Head of State in the 1980s, met with the President at about 8am on Tuesday at the State House, Abuja. “He will resume work on Wednesday,” the report said. With his appointment, Professor Gambari replaces Mallam Abba Kyari, who died last month of COVID-19. By Ismaila Chafe Abuja - President Muhammadu Buhari has dispatched a government delegation to Ilorin, Kwara State, to deliver a letter of condolence to the Emir of Ilorin, Alhaji Ibrahim Sulu-Gambari, following the loss of his mother Alhaja Aishat Zulkarnaini-Gambari. In the letter delivered by leader of the delegation, Chief… June 9, 2019 In "News" Abuja  -  A former minister of foreign affairs Prof. Ibrahim Gambari, has on Wednesday in Abuja, tasked African leaders on unity as a panacea for the development of the continent. Gambari made this known at a lecture organised by African Diplomats residing in Nigeria to commemorate African Day. He said… May 26, 2016 In "Foreign" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike has accused the Federal Government of planning to shutdown internet access during the forthcoming general elections through the Office of the National Security Adviser (NSA). He alleged that government has directed the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) to… January 31, 2019 In "News"